    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-04-12T20:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-04-12T20:00:00-05:00" n="732"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d732">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/5042: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China (<persName corresp="#p_JNT1" type="from"
                            >Johnson</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Shanghai</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-04-13T09:00:00+08:00"
                            >April 13, 1932—9 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 11:40 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The British Minister has just received a message from the local office of the
                    Ministry of Foreign Affairs to the effect that <persName corresp="#p_QT1"
                        >Quo</persName> learns from Nanking that the Chinese Government has
                    telegraphed to the Chinese delegate at Geneva to ask for an elucidation of the
                    question of the time limit. Pending a reply from Geneva on this point, the <pb
                        facs="0793" n="689" xml:id="pg_689"/> Chinese Government desires the next
                    meeting of the conference be postponed for a few days.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_JNT1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
